cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.PL

The paper deals with game theory and algorithms for solving games, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). It also involves artificial intelligence techniques for solving these games, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. The use of recursive algorithms suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also deals with the qualitative analysis of parity games, which falls under the category of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the paper involves the synthesis of different algorithms, which could fall under the category of cs.PL (Programming Languages).
